= 1.3 update & bugfix "DYNE:TRAX"
 - Revamped streaming tools with Ogg/Vorbis audio
   trasmission fully supported now! for a 100% free
   radio, now dyne:bolic comes with the latest version
   of MuSE and Icecast streaming software.
 - bug fix to nesting
 - updated software: Audacity-1.2, dvgrab-1.5, MuSE-0.9,
   Kino-0.6.5, Blender-2.32, Cinelerra-1.1.9, Icecast2,
   litestream-1.2, XChat-2.0.8, FreeJ-0.6.1-cvs
 - new software: Avidemux-2.0.22, Ghostscript-7.05
 - new games: Gnu Arcade Volley
 - mufhd0

= 1.2 milestone "DYNE:TRAX"
 - dockable system: dynebolic can run from harddisk,
   simply copying the /dyne dir on your partition.
   It goes much faster then, especially on xbox.
 - [dyne:trax] sound production suite:
   native ALSA + JACK low latency rackable sound studio
   audio software included:
   alsa-patch-bay-1.0, cheesetracker-0.9.1,
   freqtweak-0.5.3, jack-rack-1.4.3, ladcca-0.4,
   qjackctl-0.2.4, Soundtracker-0.6.7,
   spiralsyntmodular-0.2.2, pd-0.37-1test6 with
   iemlib, zexy and GEM, Hydrogen.
 - new software: JahShaka-1.9a5, jack-0.94 (dyne:trax)
   Scribus-1.0.1, Firewallbuilder-1.1.2, potrace-1.2,
   Mutt-1.5.6i, OpenMash (mbone conferencing tools),
   xvidcap-1.1.3, Transcode-0.6.12, Gringotts-1.2.7
 - updated software: Mpeg4Ip-1.0, RDesktop-1.3.1,
   Rezound-0.9b, Palantir-2.5.4, FreeJ-0.6.1-cvs,
   Firefox-0.8, Gtk-2.2.4, GnuPG-1.2.4, Gpa-0.7-cvs,
   Sylpheed-0.9.9, xmms-1.2.9, qt-3.3, AbiWord-2.0.5,
   TerminatorX-3.81
 - more devices supported: usbvision, scpca5xx, acx100
   and all other vanilla upgrades in kernel 2.4.22
 - new games: Liquidwar-5.6.1, Wesnoth-0.6.99.2
 - video and audio extras
 - removed software: Trommler (subst with Hydrogen)
 - rewrite of startup files, taschino2 nesting utility

= 1.1.1 bugfix "MAKROLAB"
 - iso format fixed to boot on AWARD bios
 - fix to pam auth: added missing /etc/security
 - new tools: stty

= 1.1 major bugfix "MAKROLAB" (bugfix)
 - fixes to: nesting mechanism, openmosix config file,
   adsl-start script, iptables libraries path, wm menu,
   net configure script for multiple devices
 - upgraded gpgme and gpa, restored GnuPG in Sylpheed
 - X is now restartable (ZAP with ctrl-alt-backspace)
 - new X resolution 1280x1024
 - pci.ids device database updated
 - upgrade to palantir 2.5.3 and fix to config path
 - btaudio soundcards set as secondary audio devices

= 1.0 milestone "MAKROLAB"
 - openmosix clustering support (also for xbox!)
 - DRI 3d accelleration on matrox, intel and other cards
 - new softwares: iceage, mjpegtools, most, gvidm, LiVES,
   e2undel, ntfstools, parted
 - new games: armagetron
 - updated software: perl-5.8.0, irssi-0.8.6, XFree86-4.3
   cardmgr-3.2.3, sylpheed-0.9.6, vim-6.2, e2fsprofs-1.34
 - more supported vga cards and fixes to autodetection
 - fixes to nesting procedure and keyboard setting
 - fix to publicvoice.fm login procedure
 - interactive debug mode at startup 
 - xbox fixes: network, audio, joypad
 
= 1.0 beta "OTOLKULTIVATOR"
 - new NESTING mechanism that lets you save your /home
   and data on harddisk or usb storage, also with pass
   protection thru AES128 filesystem encryption.
 - localization support: many languages now supported
 - new network configuration tool
 - support for automounting of usb dongles and cameras
 - new softwares: ffmpeg, WPrefs, figlet, arp, xf86cfg,
   trommler, mkfs tools, cfdisk, badblocks, dosfstools,
   grip, gcombust, silc, dvgrab, kino, vic-openmash, exim
 - updated softwares: mplayer-0.90, mozilla firebird,
   rezound-0.8, gmudix-0.10, MuSE-0.8.1-cvs, FreeJ-0.5.1,
   HasciiCam-0.9.1, cinelerra-cvs, xpdf-2.02pl1
 - new libs: quicktime, openquicktime, Xvid
 - new games: foobillard, cannonsmash
 - more documentation
 - rewrite & cleanup of major parts of the rc files
 - fixes to:
   automount module loading, many new vga cards,
   soundcards when secondary dsp is present (bttv),
   cupsd, windowmaker configuration, /etc/modules*,
   resolv.conf, csh, freej, iptables, monitor refresh,
   logging and bugreporting, shutdown and cd ejection,
   nforce ethernet,
 - new d:b chiptune jingle by dixan

